14
00:00:06.310 --> 00:00:07.900
Thank you.

15
00:00:07.900 --> 00:00:10.120
You look so happy, it makes me enjoy it too!

16
00:00:10.120 --> 00:00:12.690
Must be your upcoming-wedding aura.

17
00:00:12.690 --> 00:00:14.290
N-Nothing like that.

18
00:00:16.180 --> 00:00:19.570
<i>Would it be so wrong if we </i>did<i> get married?</i>

19
00:00:20.130 --> 00:00:23.630
<i>Once I start thinking about that, 
it's all I think about.</i>

20
00:00:23.630 --> 00:00:26.400
<i>I wonder what Honjoji-san thinks about it.</i>

21
00:00:26.400 --> 00:00:29.730
Okay, keep doing this same thing 
for another month.

22
00:00:29.730 --> 00:00:31.230
Y-Yes, ma'am.

23
00:00:31.230 --> 00:00:32.700
Well, let's keep at it.

24
00:00:32.700 --> 00:00:33.890
Uh, right.

25
00:00:34.750 --> 00:00:36.350
Didn't I tell you?

26
00:00:36.350 --> 00:00:38.940
Those two aren't in a fake engagement.

27
00:00:37.930 --> 00:00:41.520
Mamaru

28
00:00:38.940 --> 00:00:41.520
I'm not the one who said so.

29
00:00:41.520 --> 00:00:44.160
The head office wanted to make sure.

30
00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:46.240
They said you never know with young people.

31
00:00:46.240 --> 00:00:48.340
And I say again, it's not fake!

32
00:00:48.770 --> 00:00:52.350
I guess that means it'll be this kid.

33
00:00:50.150 --> 00:00:51.980
Post:

34
00:00:50.150 --> 00:00:52.660
Kinshicho Branch

35
00:00:50.150 --> 00:00:52.660
Age:

36
00:00:50.150 --> 00:00:52.660
Hire Date:

37
00:00:53.840 --> 00:00:56.080
Does it really have to be one of ours?

38
00:00:56.080 --> 00:00:57.970
Make up your mind already!

39
00:00:57.970 --> 00:01:00.080
<i>Somebody</i> has to go there!

40
00:01:00.340 --> 00:01:02.720
I mean, I know nobody 
wants to go anywhere cold.

41
00:01:02.720 --> 00:01:06.090
But we also can't open 
an empty branch, now can we?

42
00:01:06.320 --> 00:01:11.540
All we need is your okay to go this route, 
so could you finalize things soon?

43
00:01:11.840 --> 00:01:14.600
Name: 
Gonda

44
00:01:13.920 --> 00:01:16.430
What?! Me, go to Alaska?!

45
00:01:16.430 --> 00:01:17.970
Looks like it.

46
00:01:17.970 --> 00:01:20.670
W-Wait a minute! It's been decided?!

47
00:01:20.670 --> 00:01:22.810
Well, it's a rumor anyway.

48
00:01:22.810 --> 00:01:25.590
But that's what someone 
at the head office said.

49
00:01:25.590 --> 00:01:28.080
But I haven't even been told yet!

50
00:01:28.080 --> 00:01:31.000
What's a good farewell gift? A down jacket?

51
00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:33.780
Give me a break, Keisuke-san!

52
00:01:34.290 --> 00:01:36.750
Th-This can't be true, can it?

53
00:01:36.750 --> 00:01:38.750
It's not true, right?

54
00:01:38.750 --> 00:01:40.000
<i>Gonda?</i>

55
00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:41.920
<i>Going to Anchorage?</i>

56
00:01:43.500 --> 00:01:47.880
Are You Really Getting Married?

57
00:01:53.050 --> 00:01:55.310
<i>What am I doing turning a blind eye?</i>

58
00:01:55.310 --> 00:01:57.810
<i>I must have known it 
would turn out like this!</i>

59
00:01:58.110 --> 00:02:02.000
<i>Thanks to our false plan, somebody 
else will be going to Anchorage.</i>

60
00:02:00.310 --> 00:02:02.310
297 days until the
 Anchorage Branch opens

61
00:02:04.520 --> 00:02:07.920
<i>Sending Gonda away now seems unthinkable!</i>

62
00:02:09.840 --> 00:02:11.890
<i>Should things end this way?!</i>

63
00:02:10.780 --> 00:02:12.650
Blog 5

64
00:02:10.780 --> 00:02:12.650
Coming up with new plans!

65
00:02:14.890 --> 00:02:20.240
Ohara-kun, you think the rumor 
about Gonda-kun is true?

66
00:02:25.830 --> 00:02:28.130
<i>There's nothing wrong with this scheme.</i>

67
00:02:28.530 --> 00:02:33.650
<i>Honjoji-san's plan is perfect, 
and we needed it at the time.</i>

68
00:02:34.280 --> 00:02:37.510
<i>I just didn't bother to imagine...</i>

69
00:02:37.840 --> 00:02:42.520
<i>It's not just Gonda. 
Nobody should have to go in our place!</i>

70
00:02:42.790 --> 00:02:45.110
<i>I didn't see it at all.</i>

71
00:02:45.110 --> 00:02:47.270
<i>I'm not the only one 
who'd be inconvenienced.</i>

72
00:02:47.750 --> 00:02:49.200
<i>Everyone's the same.</i>

73
00:02:49.200 --> 00:02:52.540
<i>They're all living their lives 
the best they can!</i>

74
00:02:55.990 --> 00:03:00.240
<i>It was thanks to this scheme 
that I picked up on that.</i>

75
00:03:00.980 --> 00:03:02.790
<i>Thanks to Honjoji-san.</i>

76
00:03:15.470 --> 00:03:17.530
Kurokawa-san, do you have a minute?

77
00:03:19.760 --> 00:03:21.250
Ohara?

78
00:03:21.250 --> 00:03:23.360
There's something I want to tell you.

79
00:03:24.890 --> 00:03:28.820
<i>I'm going to tell her our marriage is a lie.</i>

80
00:03:29.180 --> 00:03:32.870
<i>I'll put an end to the whole thing.</i>

81
00:03:33.840 --> 00:03:35.150
Tell me what?

82
00:03:36.870 --> 00:03:39.910
<i>You know, something like this 
happened before.</i>

83
00:03:42.120 --> 00:03:45.250
<i>The day the pool opened when I was a kid.</i>

84
00:03:45.250 --> 00:03:47.870
Public Pool

85
00:03:46.480 --> 00:03:49.990
<i>On the way home, there was 
a grilled squid food truck.</i>

86
00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:50.380
Grilled 
Squid

87
00:03:50.850 --> 00:03:53.890
<i>It was free to use the pool 
on its opening day.</i>

88
00:03:53.890 --> 00:03:58.080
<i>But my mother made me bring 
some money, just in case.</i>

89
00:03:58.080 --> 00:04:00.760
Don't go spendin' this 
on food or nothin', now.

90
00:04:02.430 --> 00:04:03.300
But...

91
00:04:07.880 --> 00:04:09.290
Taku-chan.

92
00:04:10.410 --> 00:04:11.570
Mom!

93
00:04:11.570 --> 00:04:13.220
You have fun at the pool?

94
00:04:13.220 --> 00:04:13.900
Yep.

95
00:04:13.900 --> 00:04:18.860
U-Uh, today, you hadta pay to 
get in, so I spent the money.

96
00:04:18.860 --> 00:04:20.020
Oh.

97
00:04:20.630 --> 00:04:23.790
What's that on your mouth? Looks like sauce.

98
00:04:23.790 --> 00:04:24.680
Huh?

99
00:04:25.770 --> 00:04:26.940
Takuya.

100
00:04:26.940 --> 00:04:29.700
I'm not angry because you bought food.

101
00:04:29.700 --> 00:04:33.660
That was bad too, but why'd you 
lie about needin' the money?

102
00:04:33.660 --> 00:04:37.110
You knew you'd done a bad thing, 
and you tried to hide it.

103
00:04:37.110 --> 00:04:39.640
<i>That's</i> what I have a hard time forgivin'.

104
00:04:40.450 --> 00:04:45.370
Takuya, do you know full well 
why you got in trouble?

105
00:04:46.770 --> 00:04:49.890
Tell me in your own words.

106
00:04:51.510 --> 00:04:55.230
Uh, I went to the pool with my friends.

107
00:04:55.650 --> 00:04:58.650
After, there was this grilled squid.

108
00:04:59.650 --> 00:05:04.010
Uh, I bought some with 
Mom's money and ate it.

109
00:05:05.120 --> 00:05:06.760
A-And then...

110
00:05:08.290 --> 00:05:13.450
I lied to Mom and said
 that I spent it on the pool.

111
00:05:19.330 --> 00:05:21.830
<i>It wasn't so much that I bought the food.</i>

112
00:05:21.830 --> 00:05:28.390
<i>It was that I lied to cover it up 
that made me cry from shame.</i>

113
00:05:30.770 --> 00:05:34.190
<i>I haven't grown up at all, have I?</i>

114
00:05:37.710 --> 00:05:39.070
Kurokawa-san.

115
00:05:39.070 --> 00:05:41.910
I'm not getting married at all.

116
00:05:41.910 --> 00:05:42.820
Huh?

117
00:05:42.820 --> 00:05:45.850
I-I was lying.

118
00:05:45.850 --> 00:05:50.080
I didn't want to go to Anchorage, 
so I faked an engagement.

119
00:05:50.550 --> 00:05:53.750
I gave no consideration to anyone else.

120
00:05:53.750 --> 00:05:55.360
I deceived everyone!

121
00:05:56.640 --> 00:05:59.840
I truly am sorry!

122
00:06:00.240 --> 00:06:03.600
I'll be the one to go to Anchorage!

123
00:06:05.620 --> 00:06:07.090
Okay, I hear you.

124
00:06:07.970 --> 00:06:09.400
Come with me now.

125
00:06:13.570 --> 00:06:14.530
In here.

126
00:06:22.490 --> 00:06:23.820
Honjoji-san?

127
00:06:24.660 --> 00:06:29.670
As it turns out, she told me 
the very same thing earlier.

128
00:06:29.670 --> 00:06:32.160
That your marriage wasn't real.

129
00:06:32.160 --> 00:06:35.290
And that she would go to Anchorage.

130
00:06:35.290 --> 00:06:37.550
Looks like neither of you 
knew about this part.

131
00:06:38.380 --> 00:06:42.320
In other words, you both wanted to 
avoid going to Anchorage so much,

132
00:06:42.320 --> 00:06:44.200
you lied about getting married?

133
00:06:45.120 --> 00:06:46.430
That's right.

134
00:06:49.700 --> 00:06:52.170
I couldn't tell one bit!

135
00:06:52.170 --> 00:06:54.700
Looks like you were 
stressing big-time over this.

136
00:06:55.510 --> 00:06:57.940
But you don't need to worry anymore.

137
00:06:59.290 --> 00:07:01.820
<i>I'll</i> go to Anchorage!

138
00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:03.950
What?!

139
00:07:03.950 --> 00:07:05.950
Don't make a fuss.

140
00:07:05.950 --> 00:07:11.580
I've already told the head office, 
so you two won't have to go anywhere.

141
00:07:11.580 --> 00:07:13.470
So, back to work!

142
00:07:13.470 --> 00:07:14.700
Carry these!

143
00:07:14.700 --> 00:07:15.630
Make it snappy!

144
00:07:19.750 --> 00:07:21.870
295 days until the
 Anchorage Branch opens

145
00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:24.760
<i>Kurokawa-san's going to Anchorage?</i>

146
00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:28.710
<i>This settles things... but that's not okay!</i>

147
00:07:27.760 --> 00:07:29.010
not good

148
00:07:29.010 --> 00:07:31.970
Please donate funds for Gonda's down jacket.

149
00:07:31.970 --> 00:07:36.140
Keisuke-san! It's still not a done deal 
that I'm going to Alaska!

150
00:07:36.140 --> 00:07:38.650
Oh, but Gonda-kun's a big guy. 
Wouldn't a sweater be enough?

151
00:07:42.910 --> 00:07:45.260
Sorry to drag you out here.

152
00:07:45.260 --> 00:07:46.010
It's fine.

153
00:07:46.010 --> 00:07:48.740
I figured you might be concerned.

154
00:07:49.110 --> 00:07:52.380
About the fact that I'm going in your place.

155
00:07:52.380 --> 00:07:53.860
Very concerned!

156
00:07:53.860 --> 00:07:57.120
Without you, what will become 
of the Kinshicho Branch?

157
00:07:57.480 --> 00:07:59.690
Our branch will be fine.

158
00:07:59.690 --> 00:08:01.550
Everyone there is outstanding.

159
00:08:01.550 --> 00:08:02.970
And besides...

160
00:08:07.100 --> 00:08:09.380
Right now I'm excited!

161
00:08:09.380 --> 00:08:11.890
Because I get to go on another journey!

162
00:08:12.470 --> 00:08:15.270
I used to spend all my time traveling.

163
00:08:15.760 --> 00:08:19.100
Asia, Africa, Europe—all over the world.

164
00:08:19.490 --> 00:08:22.110
I love the sea, and 
I've seen so much.

165
00:08:22.470 --> 00:08:24.340
Isn't it the same for you two?

166
00:08:24.340 --> 00:08:26.860
You came to this company 
because you love traveling.

167
00:08:27.170 --> 00:08:30.440
But now I'm married and running a branch.

168
00:08:30.440 --> 00:08:33.740
I help others travel, 
but I no longer do it myself.

169
00:08:34.100 --> 00:08:37.940
I spend every day in meetings, 
I manage projects and figures,

170
00:08:37.940 --> 00:08:40.370
and I make my employees do unpleasant tasks.

171
00:08:40.680 --> 00:08:43.960
Once I get home, I'm a good wife 
and daughter-in-law.

172
00:08:43.960 --> 00:08:46.130
I have to balance work and home life.

173
00:08:46.590 --> 00:08:49.400
I treat myself with one trip 
a year to the Maldives.

174
00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:52.290
It's not that I hate that arrangement.

175
00:08:52.290 --> 00:08:53.890
It's just, it occurs to me...

176
00:08:54.560 --> 00:08:58.020
There's a clear, straight road 
stretching out ahead of me.

177
00:08:58.020 --> 00:09:00.860
I walk along it, taking care 
not to step off of it.

178
00:09:01.380 --> 00:09:03.420
This is my life now?

179
00:09:04.020 --> 00:09:06.150
No, it's not!

180
00:09:06.150 --> 00:09:08.690
I need more adventure than that!

181
00:09:09.550 --> 00:09:12.610
Taking every path, 
overcoming every difficulty.

182
00:09:13.060 --> 00:09:17.770
All in the name of seeing things 
I've never seen in places I've never been.

183
00:09:20.970 --> 00:09:24.250
That's the joy of living!

184
00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:27.550
Uh, but, is your family on board with this?

185
00:09:27.550 --> 00:09:30.720
Well, we did start out as travel companions.

186
00:09:31.030 --> 00:09:33.010
Huh?! You're going to Anchorage?!

187
00:09:33.010 --> 00:09:35.790
Sorry, I've got to go cultivate Alaska.

188
00:09:35.790 --> 00:09:38.350
It's kind of a relief.

189
00:09:38.350 --> 00:09:41.910
It's like you've been stuck on the straight 
and narrow since we got married.

190
00:09:41.910 --> 00:09:44.480
I thought I might be holding you back.

191
00:09:44.480 --> 00:09:46.270
What a thing to worry about!

192
00:09:46.560 --> 00:09:50.340
I'm jealous. Maybe I'll go to Alaska too.

193
00:09:51.280 --> 00:09:53.160
You're welcome anytime.

194
00:09:53.410 --> 00:09:57.060
And so, other than my 
husband's family, no worries.

195
00:09:57.060 --> 00:09:58.910
I-Is that so?

196
00:10:01.720 --> 00:10:03.610
Thanks for coming out here with me.

197
00:10:08.620 --> 00:10:14.100
Kurokawa-san said all that, but 
does it really have nothing to do with us?

198
00:10:14.100 --> 00:10:15.890
That I don't know.

199
00:10:16.350 --> 00:10:19.380
But it seemed like she was telling the truth.

200
00:10:19.970 --> 00:10:22.230
<i>"Things I've never seen," huh?</i>

201
00:10:23.600 --> 00:10:25.500
<i>I get that, now.</i>

202
00:10:25.980 --> 00:10:30.730
<i>We've been on the biggest journey 
of our lives, these past two months.</i>

203
00:10:31.640 --> 00:10:35.990
Well, there's no longer 
any need for our plan.

204
00:10:42.190 --> 00:10:43.870
Thanks for all you've done.

205
00:10:45.260 --> 00:10:48.720
<i>Thus, our journey came to an end.</i>

206
00:10:52.010 --> 00:10:55.510
Maybe it's for the best 
that this plan is over.

207
00:10:56.060 --> 00:10:59.000
I doubt it would have worked until the end.

208
00:10:59.390 --> 00:11:02.600
It isn't good to go on lying indefinitely.

209
00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:06.270
That's true. Let's put an end to the lies.

210
00:11:06.580 --> 00:11:09.550
And let's think about what happens next.

211
00:11:09.550 --> 00:11:10.770
All right.

212
00:11:10.770 --> 00:11:12.530
Inform those at work about
 the pretend marriage
 Contact Ashida-san about taking over 
Our Worthwhile JTC Life
 Return wedding gifts
 Kurokawa-san - goodie basket
 Shinshi-san - tea set
 George-san - pair of Hawaiian shirts
 Kitagawa-san - bath salts
 Isojima-san - soup set
 Saito-san - towel set
 Itsuki-san - wine
 Gonda-san - husband-and-wife chopsticks
 Komiya-san - paired glasses
 Nonoyama-san - flowers
 Should we inform Princess Claudia?
 Expense report
 Cushion ¥2090
 Globe ¥3460
 Mug ¥2000
 Toothbrush ¥620
 Desk lamp ¥2180
 Beer ¥3780
 Low table ¥2860
 Tent ¥2680

213
00:11:11.970 --> 00:11:15.030
We'll need to tell everyone 
at work that it was a lie.

214
00:11:15.030 --> 00:11:17.780
Yes, we can inform them tomorrow.

215
00:11:18.120 --> 00:11:20.360
Should we tell anyone at the head office?

216
00:11:20.360 --> 00:11:23.580
I think we'll have to tell Mamaru-san.

217
00:11:23.580 --> 00:11:26.500
Although I expect it will be rather awkward.

218
00:11:26.500 --> 00:11:28.620
Is it all right if we go together?

219
00:11:28.620 --> 00:11:30.750
O-Of course it's all right.

220
00:11:30.750 --> 00:11:31.850
Let's do that.

221
00:11:33.530 --> 00:11:36.480
Cost of the two cushions: ¥4180.

222
00:11:36.480 --> 00:11:39.390
The globe we got for the blog cost ¥3460.

223
00:11:39.390 --> 00:11:41.150
Do we include the water bill?

224
00:11:41.150 --> 00:11:43.390
Let's add everything and calculate it.

225
00:11:43.390 --> 00:11:46.770
What do we do with the table, light, etc. 
we used for the blog?

226
00:11:46.770 --> 00:11:48.840
Anything we aren't going to use, 
I'll sell online.

227
00:11:51.810 --> 00:11:54.340
That was relatively easy to sort out.

228
00:11:54.340 --> 00:11:57.000
Well, it was only two months' worth.

229
00:11:57.800 --> 00:12:00.530
It almost feels like a dream.

230
00:12:02.780 --> 00:12:04.750
Bottles

231
00:12:02.780 --> 00:12:04.750
Cans

232
00:12:04.750 --> 00:12:06.710
Plastic bottles

233
00:12:09.180 --> 00:12:12.920
I suppose actual marriage is a lot harder.

234
00:12:12.920 --> 00:12:16.130
Yes, I'm sure it is.

235
00:12:16.440 --> 00:12:20.730
Even if it's fun for a short time, being 
together all the time must be too much.

236
00:12:21.340 --> 00:12:26.000
You have to be attentive to each other 
constantly, and it's much easier to be alone.

237
00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:28.810
I feel like I'd spend an eternity fretting.

238
00:12:28.810 --> 00:12:31.460
I'd be worried about work and money too.

239
00:12:31.460 --> 00:12:35.980
And you'd no longer have time for yourself
or be free to go out whenever you want.

240
00:12:36.370 --> 00:12:39.150
Married couples probably 
also have different values,

241
00:12:39.150 --> 00:12:42.370
and there's bound to be lots 
of arguments over little things.

242
00:12:42.370 --> 00:12:45.420
Hanging out with family is troublesome too.

243
00:12:45.420 --> 00:12:49.120
It's annoying when everyone 
says "congratulations,"

244
00:12:49.120 --> 00:12:51.510
and we can do everything 
by ourselves as it is.

245
00:12:52.580 --> 00:12:55.930
The more I think about it, 
the more I reach the same conclusion.

246
00:12:55.930 --> 00:12:58.500
It's fine not to get married.

247
00:12:58.500 --> 00:13:01.600
Yes, it feels like it's nothing but risk.

248
00:13:01.600 --> 00:13:04.670
It takes so much effort 
to live on your own as it is.

249
00:13:04.670 --> 00:13:06.790
So, to have to support someone else?

250
00:13:07.850 --> 00:13:11.220
Marriage is all an illusion.

251
00:13:15.940 --> 00:13:18.350
Well, the trains will start running soon.

252
00:13:18.350 --> 00:13:19.310
Right.

253
00:13:43.890 --> 00:13:46.720
<i>A straight road continues on and on.</i>

254
00:13:47.290 --> 00:13:50.620
<i>I just keep on walking, 
taking care not to leave that road.</i>

255
00:13:51.230 --> 00:13:53.450
<i>This is my life...</i>

256
00:14:09.000 --> 00:14:10.130
Honjoji-san!

257
00:14:10.410 --> 00:14:13.550
Honjoji-san!

258
00:14:19.890 --> 00:14:25.990
U-Um, we're just coworkers. 
Not even friends.

259
00:14:34.350 --> 00:14:36.350
But can we get married anyway?!

260
00:14:45.620 --> 00:14:47.120
Y-Yes, we can!

261
00:14:47.490 --> 00:14:51.210
We aren't even going out, 
but can we get married?!

262
00:14:51.210 --> 00:14:52.290
Yes, we can!

263
00:14:52.290 --> 00:14:57.130
Nothing amazing's happened to us like 
in a TV show, but can we get married?!

264
00:14:57.130 --> 00:14:57.880
Yes, we can!

265
00:14:57.880 --> 00:15:03.630
Maybe we didn't have any fated encounter or 
anything, but can we get married anyway?!

266
00:15:03.630 --> 00:15:05.380
Yes, we can!

267
00:15:10.700 --> 00:15:12.840
Please just tell me one thing.

268
00:15:14.250 --> 00:15:17.150
Do you love me?

269
00:15:18.780 --> 00:15:23.410
I do so many weird things, 
and I'm always regretting it.

270
00:15:23.410 --> 00:15:25.550
I have no confidence in myself.

271
00:15:26.050 --> 00:15:32.450
But the truth is, there are many things 
I want to do and talk about with someone.

272
00:15:34.370 --> 00:15:37.040
I do love you, Honjoji-san!

273
00:15:42.280 --> 00:15:46.050
And I... love you, Ohara-kun!

274
00:15:52.310 --> 00:15:55.120
I was thinking marriage was the finish line.

275
00:15:55.750 --> 00:15:59.140
But it's really a beginning, isn't it?

276
00:15:59.630 --> 00:16:01.300
That's right.

277
00:16:01.300 --> 00:16:03.560
You can begin at any time.

278
00:16:05.080 --> 00:16:08.200
And so, Honjoji-san. Once again...

279
00:16:09.240 --> 00:16:10.910
You can call me "Rika."

280
00:16:12.510 --> 00:16:13.370
Okay.

281
00:16:13.830 --> 00:16:16.630
R-R-R...

282
00:16:16.630 --> 00:16:17.750
R...

283
00:16:18.220 --> 00:16:21.730
Rika-san, will you marry me?

284
00:16:24.220 --> 00:16:25.250
Yes.

285
00:16:28.630 --> 00:16:31.550
Let's start over again!

286
00:16:31.550 --> 00:16:32.260
Yes.

287
00:16:40.790 --> 00:16:43.070
So, Ohara-kun, first things first.

288
00:16:43.070 --> 00:16:45.360
Oh, so I'm still "Ohara-kun."

289
00:16:45.360 --> 00:16:49.510
Let's go apologize to everyone at JTC.

290
00:16:49.510 --> 00:16:50.400
